  "description_html": "<ul>\n<li>Drone Racing is an exciting technical event where teams design, build, and manually fly their own quadcopters through a challenging obstacle race track.</li>\n<li>The goal is simple: complete the track in the shortest time while correctly passing all obstacles in sequence.</li>\n<li>Each team must build its own drone and pilot it using direct visual control, making it a true hands-on engineering challenge.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The competition is conducted in two rounds:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>A qualification round to identify strong teams</li>\n<li>A final round with stricter rules and greater difficulty</li>\n<li>Teams earn points by successfully completing obstacles, maintaining accuracy, and finishing within time limits. Faster and cleaner runs score higher, while mistakes and crashes lead to penalties.</li>\n</ul>",
